HEADWORD: Dika
<hw>Di"ka</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native West African
name.]</ety> <def>A kind of food, made from the almondlike seeds of the
<spn>Irvingia Barteri</spn>, much used by natives of the west coast of
Africa; -- called also <altname>dika bread</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dike</ent>⟦br⟧
